Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Portcode is distributed as a compiled Windows binary and therefore incorporates
third-party open-source software. Each such component remains under its own
license. The authoritative, complete list of dependencies and their versions is
recorded in the project's manifests and lockfiles:

  - Rust crates:  src-tauri/Cargo.toml  and  src-tauri/Cargo.lock
  - JavaScript:   package.json          and  pnpm-lock.yaml

Notable bundled or linked components include (non-exhaustive):

  - Tauri and the Tauri plugins (Apache-2.0 OR MIT)
  - Tokio, reqwest, serde, anyhow, thiserror, uuid (Apache-2.0 OR MIT)
  - rusqlite / SQLite (SQLite is in the public domain; rusqlite is MIT)
  - keyring (Apache-2.0 OR MIT)
  - regex, globset, ignore, similar (Apache-2.0 OR MIT)
  - React and React DOM (MIT)
  - react-markdown, remark-gfm, rehype-highlight (MIT)
  - Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS (MIT)

A machine-readable Software Bill of Materials (CycloneDX) is generated and
published alongside each release. See docs/RELEASE.md for the release process.
